data.name: UTF1
data.value: FamilyLines has full support for the UTF-8 encoding format. Unfortunately most GEDCOM files are not encoded in this format so during import, FamilyLines removes characters which it may not be able to display. If you use a language which has extended character sets, some information may be lost.
